.TH "register_ftrace_function" 9 "register_ftrace_function" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
register_ftrace_function \- register a function for profiling @ops - ops structure that holds the function for profiling.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" register_ftrace_function
.BI "(struct ftrace_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ops" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Register a function to be called by all functions in the
kernel.
.SH "NOTE"
\fIops->func\fP and all the functions it calls must be labeled
with "notrace", otherwise it will go into a
recursive loop.
